  "doc_id": "37308",
  "text": "We investigate a few resampling-based methods for testing homogeneity in covariance or correlation matrices in both single-and multiple-testing settings. The H-D and nonrobust H-I bootstrap approaches using the determinantbased statistic for testing equal covariance are essentially equivalent to those proposed by [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , and our simulation results are similar to theirs. Zhu et al.used a slightly different H-D bootstrap, which fixes the scaling matrix V 1/2 at the observed value. We were not able to replicate their simulation results, and therefore no comparison was made between our methods and theirs.",
